  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - By reason of insufficient evidence provided the applicant has failed to demonstrate that the unit has been vacant for a continuous period of at least 3 months immediately prior to the date of the application for prior approval. The proposal would therefore fail to comply with Condition MA.1(a) of Part 3, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed development would fail to provide acceptable natural light levels for all habitable rooms resulting in harm to the residential amenity of future occupiers. Therefore, the proposed development fails to comply with Condition MA.2(f) of Part 3, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) and policy DMS1 of the Development Management Policies Document (2016). It would also fail to meet emerging policy LP2 of the Local Plan Publication Version (2022). \r\n",
    "Reason : 3 - There is insufficient internal floor space provided as the proposed scheme would require a minimum of 70sqm require to provide residential accommodation in line with Paragraphs 9(A) and 9(B) of Article 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\n",
    "Reason : 3 - There is insufficient internal floor space provided as the proposed scheme would require a minimum of 70sqm require to provide residential accommodation in line with Paragraphs 9(A) and 9(B) of Article 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\n",
    "Reason : 4 - The local planning authority is not satisfied that the proposed external alterations fall within any part of Class MA of Part 3, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 (as amended) and therefore require planning permission.   \r\n"
  ],
